{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501778","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501778"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:33:52+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:33:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1789"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1789"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.03,0.06,0.78,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1789"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43025"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1789"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1789"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28008"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1186"},{"type":"tags","id":"2143"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"6034"},{"type":"tags","id":"6275"},{"type":"tags","id":"6292"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5351"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6024"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42403"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43104"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43025","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43025"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 75-year-old woman is brought into the Emergency Department after a witnessed fall on to her left arm. The patient reports that she tripped on the back garden step, using her left hand to break her fall. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, there is dorsal displacement and angulation approximately three centimetres proximal to the radio-carpal joint. X-rays are performed (Image 1 - 2).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Smith\u0027s fracture","Volar Barton\u0027s fracture","Dorsal Barton\u0027s fracture","Colles fracture","Galeazzi fracture"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe answers are all types of fractures to the distal radius but differ in fracture type, presentation and mechanism of injury. \u003Cstrong\u003EColles fracture\u003C/strong\u003E is a very common complete fracture of the distal radius, it is an extra-articular fracture. The mechanism of action is commonly falling onto an extended hand and presents with dorsal angulation. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmith\u0027s fracture\u003C/strong\u003E can be thought of as the \u0027reverse Colles\u0027 fracture, it is also a complete extra-articular fracture of the distal radius however the mechanism of injury occurs from falling onto a flexed hand. Typically it presents with volar angulation. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003EBarton\u0027s fracture \u003C/strong\u003Eis an intra-articular fracture, involving the radio-carpal joint. It has a similar mechanism of injury to a Colles fracture, however, the fracture extends through the dorsal aspect of the distal radius and preserves the volar aspect of the distal radius. Commonly it presents with radio-carpal subluxation or dislocation. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVolar Barton\u0027s\u003C/strong\u003E fracture is the opposite of dorsal Barton\u0027s fracture. It is an intra-articular fracture through the volar aspect of the distal radius, commonly presenting with volar displacement. The mechanism of injury is commonly from falling onto a flexed hand. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGaleazzi fracture \u003C/strong\u003Eis a midshaft/distal fracture of the radius with dislocation of the radio-ulnar joint, the ulnar is preserved. Typically this results from falling onto an extended hand with a hyper-pronated forearm.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Colles fracture is a very common distal radial fracture resulting from falling onto an outstretched hand"],"references":["Eiff MP, Hatch RL, Calmbach WL. Carpal fractures. In: Fracture Management for Primary Care, 2nd ed, Saunders, Philadelphia 2003.","Vogt MT, Cauley JA, Tomaino MM, Stone K, Williams JR, Herndon JH. Distal radius fractures in older women: a 10-year follow-up study of descriptive characteristics and risk factors. The study of osteoporotic fractures. J Am Geriatr Soc. 2002;50(1):97-103. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12028253/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28008"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1789"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15161"},{"type":"media","id":"15162"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15161"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/db4f9332-bfe4-4147-8ca1-5707356597fd.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/db4f9332-bfe4-4147-8ca1-5707356597fd.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":543,"height":342}},{"type":"media","id":"15162","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15162"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/28fd3afb-c96c-4aff-be19-70b14883bb62.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/28fd3afb